Iron.why: A lack of iron can lead to a decrease in oxygenation of the scalp, causing hair follicles to not receive the necessary nutrients for growth, ultimately leading to hair loss.
Iron.tip: Increase iron absorption by consuming vitamin C-rich foods (like citrus fruits or bell peppers) along with iron-rich foods.

Biotin.why: A lack of biotin can disrupt the hair growth cycle, leading to hair loss, as biotin plays a crucial role in the production of keratin, a protein that makes up hair.
Biotin.tip: Use gentle hair care products and avoid heat styling to minimize hair damage.

Zinc.why: A lack of zinc can impair the hair growth cycle and lead to hair loss, as zinc is essential for the health of the hair follicles and the maintenance of the scalp.
Zinc.tip: Manage stress through relaxation techniques like meditation or yoga, as high stress levels can exacerbate hair loss.
